POSTMAN (OR THUNDER CLIENT)
1. For testing your backend API routes independently before connecting the frontend
2. Download: https://www.postman.com/downloads
3. (Alternative: Thunder Client is a VS Code extension — lighter weight, no separate app)

#These get installed inside the project folders with npm install, not system-wide:
1. Express, Mongoose, bcrypt, crypto-js, jsonwebtoken (backend)
2. React, Framer Motion, Chart.js, Axios (frontend)

  <<<---------INSTALLATION---------->>>

npm install express mongoose dotenv cors bcryptjs jsonwebtoken crypto-js
npm install -D nodemon
what it does -
1. express — server framework
2. mongoose — MongoDB connection/models
3. dotenv — load secrets from .env file
4. cors — allow frontend to talk to backend
5. bcryptjs — hash passwords (pure JS, no build tools needed — easier than bcrypt)
6. jsonwebtoken — login sessions (JWT)
7. crypto-js — AES-256 encryption for journal entries
8. nodemon (dev only) — auto-restarts server when you save files

npm create vite@latest frontend
what it does -
1. vite@latest — it download react vite project and latest one 
2. frontend — it will also create a new folder named as frontend due to (create in the starting in the statement)

npm install axios react-router-dom framer-motion chart.js react-chartjs-2
what it does -
1. axios — call your backend API
2. react-router-dom — page navigation (login, dashboard, journal, etc.)
3. framer-motion — the breathing animation
4. chart.js + react-chartjs-2 — mood graphs

AFTER DOWNLOADING THE ALL PACKAGES WE HAVE TO RUN BOTH (IN SEPERATE TERMINAL) :
# Terminal 1 - backend
cd backend
npx nodemon server.js

# Terminal 2 - frontend
cd frontend
npm run dev


